---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';

const pullRequest = 'https://github.com/prasithg/claude-desktop-supervisor/pull/3';
const hostedRun = 'https://github.com/prasithg/claude-desktop-supervisor/actions/runs/29530399682';
const repository = 'https://github.com/prasithg/claude-desktop-supervisor';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Attesting a scheduler run | Prasith Govin"
  description="A field note on binding one metadata-only GitHub Actions run identity to an exact workflow, source digest, and Sigstore transparency receipt."
  ogTitle="Attesting a scheduler run"
  ogDescription="The producer, hosted signer, verifier, and denial checks behind one bounded scheduler identity receipt."
  imageAlt="Portrait of Prasith Govin"
>
  <div class="site-shell attestation-shell" id="top">
    <SiteNav />

    <main id="main" class="attestation-note">
      <header class="attestation-hero">
        <div class="attestation-hero__meta">
          <p class="eyebrow"><span aria-hidden="true">07</span>Field note / July 2026</p>
          <span class="attestation-status"><i aria-hidden="true"></i>Open PR / attested run</span>
        </div>
        <h1>One workflow. One signed identity.</h1>
        <p class="attestation-lead">
          I needed a scheduler receipt that could survive outside the machine that wrote it. The build now emits
          one metadata-only identity, signs its digest through GitHub Actions OIDC and Sigstore, and verifies the
          repository, workflow, source, runner, subject, and transparency record downstream.
        </p>
        <ul class="attestation-boundaries" aria-label="Attestation boundaries">
          <li>Event: pull request</li>
          <li>Run: 29530399682</li>
          <li>Authority: provenance only</li>
        </ul>
      </header>

      <section class="attestation-section attestation-section--split" aria-labelledby="failure-title">
        <div>
          <p class="attestation-index">01 / THE GAP</p>
          <h2 id="failure-title">Authenticated metadata was still written by the workflow under test.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="attestation-prose">
          <p>
            A bounded provider API call can prove which GitHub Actions run completed. A local checksum can show
            that a receipt did not drift after capture. Neither one proves that the artifact came from the exact
            workflow revision named inside it.
          </p>
          <p>
            The missing link was an identity outside the JSON itself. GitHub signs the subject digest with its
            hosted-run identity. The downstream verifier then checks that certificate and transparency entry
            against a narrow policy before it accepts the observation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="attestation-section" aria-labelledby="chain-title">
        <p class="attestation-index">02 / EVIDENCE CHAIN</p>
        <h2 id="chain-title">Four boundaries stay separate</h2>
        <ol class="attestation-chain" aria-label="Attested scheduler evidence chain">
          <li>
            <span class="attestation-chain__index">01</span>
            <div><h3>Produce</h3><p>A strict allowlist writes repository, workflow, run attempt, provider head, merge-source digest, and source ref. Logs and content stay out.</p></div>
            <strong>524 B</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="attestation-chain__index">02</span>
            <div><h3>Sign</h3><p>A GitHub-hosted runner requests OIDC identity and creates one Sigstore attestation for the exact subject digest.</p></div>
            <strong>OIDC</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="attestation-chain__index">03</span>
            <div><h3>Verify</h3><p>The consumer binds the repository, signer workflow, pull-request merge ref, source digest, hosted runner, and Rekor timestamp.</p></div>
            <strong>POLICY</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="attestation-chain__index">04</span>
            <div><h3>Deny</h3><p>A changed source digest still fails after the subject and local policy are recomputed. The external signature is the boundary that does not move.</p></div>
            <strong>EXIT 2</strong>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="attestation-section" aria-labelledby="receipt-title">
        <div class="attestation-section__heading">
          <div>
            <p class="attestation-index">03 / RECEIPT</p>
            <h2 id="receipt-title">What passed on the exact branch revision</h2>
          </div>
          <p>These counts prove the narrow producer and verifier contract. They do not turn the observation into recovery authority.</p>
        </div>
        <dl class="attestation-grid">
          <div><dt>Focused suite</dt><dd>37 focused controls</dd><span>producer, verifier, replay</span></div>
          <div><dt>Project gate</dt><dd>101 project tests</dd><span>Hermes Quality</span></div>
          <div><dt>Regression ledger</dt><dd>20 ledger cases</dd><span>37 controls replayed</span></div>
          <div><dt>Hosted identity</dt><dd>1 verified attestation</dd><span>transparency timestamp verified</span></div>
          <div><dt>Pull request</dt><dd>3 hosted checks</dd><span>green at 80b1831</span></div>
          <div><dt>Tampered subject</dt><dd>Denied</dd><span>recomputed JSON and policy</span></div>
        </dl>
      </section>

      <section class="attestation-section attestation-section--split" aria-labelledby="limits-title">
        <div>
          <p class="attestation-index">04 / AUTHORITY LIMIT</p>
          <h2 id="limits-title">A signed workflow receipt cannot approve its own recovery action.</h2>
        </div>
        <ul class="attestation-limits">
          <li><strong>This was a pull request event, not a schedule event.</strong> The receipt does not cover a timer-fired occurrence.</li>
          <li><strong>The signature proves artifact provenance.</strong> It does not prove scheduler-owner absence or an operational recovery decision.</li>
          <li><strong>The receipt is not safe for destructive recovery.</strong> Its machine field remains false.</li>
          <li><strong>The pull request remains open.</strong> The branch is public, mergeable, and green, but it is not merged into the default branch.</li>
          <li><strong>No independent model review is claimed.</strong> The review route was unavailable, so the limitation stays attached to this result.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="attestation-section attestation-sources" aria-labelledby="sources-title">
        <div>
          <p class="attestation-index">05 / PUBLIC EVIDENCE</p>
          <h2 id="sources-title">Source, review state, and hosted run</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="attestation-links">
          <a href={pullRequest} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span>Pull request</span>
            Exact branch revision and three green checks <i aria-hidden="true">↗</i>
          </a>
          <a href={hostedRun} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span>Hosted run</span>
            Run 29530399682 and the attestation job <i aria-hidden="true">↗</i>
          </a>
          <a href={repository} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            <span>Repository</span>
            Public producer source and commit history <i aria-hidden="true">↗</i>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <aside class="attestation-next" aria-label="Current status and next gate">
        <p class="attestation-index">CURRENT STATUS</p>
        <h2>The provenance chain is green on an open branch. A timer-fired run and independent review remain separate gates.</h2>
        <a class="button button--primary" href="/work/">Browse all evidence notes <span aria-hidden="true">↙</span></a>
      </aside>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <span>© 2026 Prasith Govin</span>
      <span>Signed provenance. Bounded authority.</span>
      <nav aria-label="Attestation note links"><a href="/">Home</a><a href="#top">Top ↑</a></nav>
    </footer>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .attestation-note { padding: 0 0 120px; }
  .attestation-hero { padding: clamp(100px, 12vw, 170px) 0 110px; }
  .attestation-hero__meta { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 24px; }
  .attestation-status { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; color: var(--green); font: 650 10px/1 var(--mono); letter-spacing: .06em; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .attestation-status i { width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%; background: currentColor; box-shadow: 0 0 0 5px color-mix(in srgb, currentColor 12%, transparent); }
  .attestation-hero h1 { max-width: 1120px; margin: 34px 0 36px; font-size: clamp(68px, 9.6vw, 142px); font-weight: 570; line-height: .88; letter-spacing: -.076em; text-wrap: balance; }
  .attestation-lead { max-width: 990px; margin: 0; color: var(--text-soft); font-size: clamp(20px, 2.2vw, 29px); line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: -.03em; text-wrap: pretty; }
  .attestation-boundaries { margin: 58px 0 0; padding: 18px 0; display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px 34px; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); list-style: none; }
  .attestation-boundaries li { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 9px; color: var(--muted); font: 600 10px/1.3 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; }
  .attestation-boundaries li::before { content: ''; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--amber); }
  .attestation-section { padding: 110px 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .attestation-section--split { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, .86fr) minmax(360px, 1fr); gap: clamp(60px, 10vw, 150px); }
  .attestation-index { margin: 0 0 22px; color: var(--amber); font: 650 10px/1.3 var(--mono); letter-spacing: .09em; }
  .attestation-section h2, .attestation-next h2 { max-width: 950px; margin: 0; font-size: clamp(42px, 5.4vw, 74px); font-weight: 560; line-height: .99; letter-spacing: -.06em; text-wrap: balance; }
  .attestation-prose { display: grid; gap: 24px; }
  .attestation-prose p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-soft); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.72; text-wrap: pretty; }
  .attestation-chain { margin: 64px 0 0; padding: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); list-style: none; }
  .attestation-chain li { min-height: 150px; padding: 24px 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 62px 1fr auto; gap: 26px; align-items: center; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .attestation-chain__index { color: var(--amber); font: 650 11px/1 var(--mono); }
  .attestation-chain h3 { margin: 0 0 9px; font-size: clamp(25px, 3vw, 38px); line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -.045em; }
  .attestation-chain p { max-width: 800px; margin: 0; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; }
  .attestation-chain strong { min-width: 88px; padding: 10px 12px; border: 1px solid var(--line-strong); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--text-soft); font: 650 9px/1 var(--mono); text-align: center; letter-spacing: .08em; }
  .attestation-section__heading { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr minmax(320px, 470px); align-items: end; gap: 80px; }
  .attestation-section__heading > p { margin: 0; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.65; }
  .attestation-grid { margin: 62px 0 0; display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); border-top: 1px solid var(--line); border-left: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .attestation-grid div { min-height: 230px; padding: 24px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; border-right: 1px solid var(--line); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .attestation-grid dt { color: var(--quiet); font: 600 10px/1.4 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .06em; }
  .attestation-grid dd { margin: auto 0 12px; color: var(--text); font-size: clamp(29px, 3vw, 47px); font-weight: 590; line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -.055em; }
  .attestation-grid span { color: var(--amber); font: 650 10px/1.3 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; }
  .attestation-limits { margin: 0; padding: 0; display: grid; list-style: none; }
  .attestation-limits li { padding: 22px 0 22px 32px; position: relative; border-top: 1px solid var(--line); color: var(--text-soft); font-size: 17px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .attestation-limits li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line); }
  .attestation-limits li::before { content: '×'; position: absolute; left: 3px; color: var(--amber); font: 650 18px/1 var(--mono); }
  .attestation-limits strong { color: var(--text); }
  .attestation-sources { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(280px, .7fr) 1fr; gap: clamp(60px, 10vw, 150px); }
  .attestation-links { display: grid; gap: 12px; }
  .attestation-links a { min-height: 112px; padding: 24px; display: grid; align-content: center; gap: 9px; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 10px; background: var(--surface-soft); color: var(--text-soft); }
  .attestation-links a:hover { border-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--amber) 48%, var(--line)); color: var(--text); }
  .attestation-links span { color: var(--amber); font: 650 10px/1 var(--mono); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: .08em; }
  .attestation-links i { float: right; color: var(--amber); font-style: normal; }
  .attestation-next { padding: clamp(52px, 7vw, 86px); border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 14px; background: radial-gradient(circle at 90% 10%, color-mix(in srgb, var(--amber) 10%, transparent), transparent 38%), var(--surface); }
  .attestation-next h2 { max-width: 1060px; font-size: clamp(36px, 4.8vw, 64px); }
  .attestation-next .button { margin-top: 42px; }
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .attestation-section--split, .attestation-sources { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 48px; }
    .attestation-section__heading { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 28px; }
    .attestation-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
  }
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .attestation-note { padding-bottom: 76px; }
    .attestation-hero { padding: 82px 0 76px; }
    .attestation-hero__meta { align-items: flex-start; flex-direction: column; }
    .attestation-hero h1 { margin: 26px 0 28px; font-size: clamp(54px, 17.2vw, 78px); line-height: .91; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .attestation-lead { font-size: 18px; }
    .attestation-boundaries { margin-top: 42px; align-items: flex-start; flex-direction: column; }
    .attestation-section { padding: 76px 0; }
    .attestation-chain { margin-top: 42px; }
    .attestation-chain li { grid-template-columns: 44px 1fr; gap: 18px; }
    .attestation-chain strong { grid-column: 2; width: max-content; }
    .attestation-grid { margin-top: 42px; grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .attestation-grid div { min-height: 190px; }
    .attestation-next { padding: 30px 22px; }
    .attestation-next .button { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
